[div class=p 
	[a href=https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/PICO-8 rel=noopener external nofollow 
		"PICO-8
	]a
	" is a virtual machine and game engine created by Lexaloffle Games. It is a 
	[a href=https://www.lexaloffle.com/pico-8.php?page=faq rel=noopener external nofollow 
		"fantasy video game console
	]a
	" that mimics the limited graphical and sound capabilities of 8-bit systems of the 1980s.
	$LF
]div
[div class=p 
	"PICO-8 application can run games and it can convert them to a standalone executable, whose Linux version works well in 
	(__wikiLink|displaytext=libTAS|href=/EmulatorResources/LibTAS)
	". Some developers release executable files for each platform, and some games you have to convert yourself.
	$LF
]div
[h4 id=HowToGenerateTheExecutableFile 
	" How to generate the executable file
	$LF
]h4
[ol 
	[li 
		" Open the PICO-8 client
		$LF
	]li
	[li 
		" Type 
		[code 
			"FOLDER
		]code
		$LF
	]li
	[li 
		" Drop the 
		[code 
			"gamename.p8.png
		]code
		" file for the game on this folder (replace 
		[code 
			"gamename
		]code
		" with what your game is actually called) and close the dialog
		$LF
	]li
	[li 
		" Type 
		[code 
			"LOAD gamename.p8.png
		]code
		$LF
	]li
	[li 
		" Type 
		[code 
			"EXPORT gamename.bin
		]code
		" to generate the standalone executables
		$LF
	]li
	[li 
		" Launch 
		[code 
			"gamename.bin/linux/gamename
		]code
		" from libTAS
		$LF
	]li
]ol
[div class=p 
	"Config path, in case you need it, is 
	[code 
		"~/.lexaloffle/pico-8/config.txt
	]code
	".
	$LF
]div
[h4 id=MovieSubmissions 
	" Movie submissions
	$LF
]h4
[div class=p 
	"We allow submissions using PICO-8 with libTAS. Please follow these guidelines to ensure your movie is acceptable and can be synced:
	$LF
]div
[ul 
	[li 
		" Follow all rules already in place for 
		(__wikiLink|displaytext=submitting libTAS movies|href=/EmulatorResources/LibTAS#MovieSubmissions)
		".
		$LF
	]li
]ul
[ul 
	[li 
		" 
		[b 
			"Try to use the latest version of PICO-8!
		]b
		" Although older versions are accessible after registering in the author's page with an activation key, please use the latest one.
		$LF
	]li
]ul
[ul 
	[li 
		" 
		[b 
			"Make sure your movie starts with no save data!
		]b
		" Having your own save data present may cause desyncs when other people try to run your movie. To delete your save data, clear the 
		[code 
			"~/.lexaloffle/pico-8/cdata/
		]code
		" directory.
		$LF
	]li
]ul
[ul 
	[li 
		" When making a libTAS movie that you plan to submit to TASVideos or upload it to userfiles, put 
		[code 
			"Platform: PICO8
		]code
		" (no hyphen) at the very start of the movie annotations, that way the site will recognize your platform properly.
		$LF
	]li
]ul
[ul 
	[li 
		" In your description or movie annotations, please provide the following:
		$LF
		[ul 
			[li 
				" libTAS version
				$LF
			]li
			[li 
				" PICO-8 version
				$LF
			]li
			[li 
				" Filename and MD5 hash of your 
				[code 
					".png
				]code
				" (use 
				[code 
					"md5sum yourgame.png
				]code
				" in a terminal)
				$LF
			]li
			[li 
				" Config variable 
				[code 
					"foreground_sleep_ms
				]code
				" can cause desyncs if the value doesn't match on different machines, so provide it as a part of sync info to be safe.
			]li
		]ul
	]li
]ul
